definition.value: A benzenedicarboxylic acid carrying carboxy groups at positions 1 and 4. One of three possible isomers of benzenedicarboxylic acid, the others being phthalic and isophthalic acids.
A maltose phosphate having the phosphate group placed at the 6'-position.
A beta-D-glucopyranoside with a 6-alkylamino-7-H-purin-7-yl substituent at the anomeric carbon atom.
A glycosyl alditol consistion of a D-glucopyranose and a D-manitol residue joined in sequence by a (1->1) glycosidic bond.
Any alpha-amino acid having L-configuration at the alpha-carbon.
